Most Argo CD setups fail in one critical area: identity and access management.
Local users. Shared admin credentials.
 No centralized control. No audit trail.
That does not scale.

Today I implemented enterprise-grade Single Sign-On (SSO) for Argo CD using Okta, running on Kubernetes.
What this setup delivers:
 ‚Ä¢ Centralized authentication via Okta
 ‚Ä¢ Secure SSO flow using SAML + Dex
 ‚Ä¢ Group-based RBAC inside Argo CD
 ‚Ä¢ HTTPS access via AWS ALB + ACM
 ‚Ä¢ No local users, no credential sprawl
Architecture highlights:
 Okta ‚Üí Dex ‚Üí Argo CD ‚Üí Kubernetes 
 TLS terminated at the Load Balancer
 Authorization enforced via Argo CD RBAC
This is how you move from a demo-grade Argo CD setup to a production-ready platform.

